Question: Do you think Facebook enhance quality of life? Motivate your answer.
Answer:
Whether or not Facebook enhances quality of life really depends on individual uses. Obviously, it is a good way to seek social information, maintain social relations and obtain entertainment. But the habitual use may become addictive. Some people tend to check it frequently that it diverts attention away and lowers their productivity at work. Finally, it cannot replace social interaction in real life. Misuses may actually lead to higher level of loneliness.